WEBVTT

00:00.031 --> 00:01.697
Previously on "The Arrangement"...

00:01.698 --> 00:03.366
- Megan Morrison.
- I don't know who this is.

00:03.368 --> 00:04.531
She hasn't broken out yet.

00:04.556 --> 00:06.256
Ah, right. Well, you are the producer.

00:06.281 --> 00:08.548
I'm just the guy looking out for
the Institute and Kyle's needs.

00:08.573 --> 00:10.973
- You've only got two hours.
- Until what?

00:10.975 --> 00:13.209
Until you read with Kyle West.

00:13.211 --> 00:16.212
I'm going to Oslo. It's
the only way to stop this.

00:16.213 --> 00:19.182
What makes you think
that you can stop it?

00:19.184 --> 00:20.660
That was amazing.

00:20.685 --> 00:22.611
You are amazing.

00:22.636 --> 00:24.379
The whole world wants
to work with Kyle West.

00:24.404 --> 00:25.655
He can do whatever he wants.

00:25.657 --> 00:27.423
He's into the whole self-actualizing

00:27.425 --> 00:29.358
Institute of the Higher Mind stuff.

00:29.360 --> 00:31.794
That's what makes him cult-y and weird.

00:31.796 --> 00:33.429
I don't want to go back to reality,

00:33.431 --> 00:34.931
and I won't do it quietly.

00:34.933 --> 00:37.500
He's offering you a contract marriage.

00:37.502 --> 00:39.972
If you sign this, you
are going to be able to do

00:39.997 --> 00:41.484
whatever you want.

00:43.000 --> 00:49.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:55.090 --> 00:57.274
So tell me about you. What do you do?

00:57.276 --> 00:59.677
- I am a corporate lawyer.
- Get out.

00:59.679 --> 01:01.445
- Yes, I am.
- Wow.

01:01.470 --> 01:03.057
- Hey, Terence.
- I know, I'm more into systems really.

01:03.082 --> 01:04.581
I made the call. The deal's closed.

01:04.584 --> 01:06.083
Like, the way they
function, how they work.

01:06.085 --> 01:07.952
- Oh, yeah, closer.
- What they reflect about us.

01:07.954 --> 01:10.521
So corporate law is
basically like a window

01:10.523 --> 01:12.401
into a calm state...

01:13.495 --> 01:14.915
Mind if I get your picture?

01:14.940 --> 01:16.160
Wonderful.

01:16.162 --> 01:18.262
It's Kyle. It's Kyle West!

01:18.264 --> 01:19.865
He looks so much cuter in person.

01:19.890 --> 01:22.126
I'm definitely a feminist,

01:22.151 --> 01:25.149
but as an actress trying to
get inside of the character,

01:25.174 --> 01:29.321
you have to recognize that
feminism isn't just one thing.

01:29.346 --> 01:31.321
- Right?
- In other words, you're smart.

01:31.346 --> 01:32.641
Oh.

01:32.666 --> 01:34.812
You want to know how somebody
like me wins an Oscar?

01:34.814 --> 01:37.581
- Brilliance.
- No, I'm not brilliant, sweetie.

01:37.583 --> 01:41.089
I produce movies with smart
women about smart women.

01:41.114 --> 01:42.947
Pardon me, Russell. It's time.

01:42.949 --> 01:44.849
- Ooh, thank you.
- Cheers.

01:48.888 --> 01:51.989
Ladies and gentlemen, Kyle
West and Megan Morrison.

01:53.693 --> 01:55.306
Look at this.

01:56.996 --> 01:58.821
This is crazy.

01:58.876 --> 02:00.475
Megan and I are excited you're all here

02:00.477 --> 02:02.110
for the third annual fund-raiser

02:02.135 --> 02:03.985
for the Change of Clothes Foundation.

02:05.201 --> 02:06.716
Now, all the money that we raise today

02:06.741 --> 02:09.229
will go towards realizing
the vision of fashion...

02:09.253 --> 02:11.554
as an instrument of change.

02:11.556 --> 02:13.823
Which means backing
up-and-coming designers

02:13.825 --> 02:15.925
who have pledged to abide
by strict environmental

02:15.927 --> 02:18.461
and social values as
they create their lines.

02:18.463 --> 02:21.683
We have one of these very
talented designers with us tonight,

02:21.708 --> 02:23.266
Maxwell Davis,

02:23.268 --> 02:25.201
who designed the dress
I'm very fortunate

02:25.203 --> 02:27.003
to be wearing right now.

02:27.005 --> 02:28.497
Thank you.

02:28.499 --> 02:29.649
Thank you all for coming.

02:29.674 --> 02:33.190
Please enjoy yourselves and,
uh, keep those checks coming.

02:34.538 --> 02:36.379
- Way to go.
- Megan...

02:36.381 --> 02:38.292
- I need to speak with you.
- Now?

02:38.317 --> 02:39.887
Yeah, now.

02:40.819 --> 02:42.785
Okay.

02:42.787 --> 02:44.454
That's you, right?

02:44.456 --> 02:47.323
- Oh, my God.
- What's going on?

02:57.447 --> 03:01.666
<font color="#007700">Synced and corrected by Aaronnmb</font>
www.addic7ed.com

03:01.783 --> 03:03.583
_

03:03.608 --> 03:05.942
Sweetie, your deal is going to close.

03:05.944 --> 03:07.543
I'm just gonna make the studio drop

03:07.545 --> 03:09.779
some of their offensive
ticky-tack bullshit,

03:09.781 --> 03:11.614
- then we'll be done.
- Awesome.

03:11.616 --> 03:14.017
But if the ticky-tack
bullshit is a sticking point,

03:14.019 --> 03:15.885
I mean, I-I just want to do the film.

03:15.887 --> 03:17.920
And you're going to do the film.

03:17.922 --> 03:20.374
I'm just gonna do my goddamn job first.

03:20.399 --> 03:22.413
Okay, go have fun at this party.

03:22.438 --> 03:24.014
Make everyone fall in love with you.

03:24.039 --> 03:26.306
- All right. Bye.
- And we'll talk later.

03:26.702 --> 03:28.965
This has been going on for, like, days.

03:28.967 --> 03:30.600
Do they always draw it out like this?

03:30.602 --> 03:32.402
I don't know. I need a drink.

03:32.404 --> 03:34.504
No, what you need to do...

03:34.506 --> 03:37.907
is embrace the fact that you are awesome

03:37.909 --> 03:40.343
and everyone in the whole
world finally knows who you are.

03:40.345 --> 03:43.935
All they really know is that
I'm Kyle West's girlfriend.

03:44.590 --> 03:45.881
Wait.

03:45.906 --> 03:49.315
What if that's all that I am?

03:51.122 --> 03:52.873
- I will pound you with this.
- Be careful.

03:54.547 --> 03:56.430
- Oh, my God.
- There's so many people.

03:56.461 --> 03:58.169
Oh, my God.

04:01.522 --> 04:03.630
Uh, yeah, I'll let him
know. All right, thanks.

04:03.810 --> 04:05.449
It's a little bottle-necked at the gate.

04:05.474 --> 04:06.680
Megan will be a few minutes.

04:06.705 --> 04:08.337
- Hey, you got a mint?
- Yeah.

04:08.339 --> 04:10.287
Thank you.

04:11.276 --> 04:13.042
Nice recast on the assistant.

04:13.044 --> 04:15.378
- Is he working out so far?
- So far.

04:15.380 --> 04:17.113
So I'm introducing Megan to...

04:17.115 --> 04:19.547
Adam, Linda. Anybody else?

04:19.572 --> 04:20.738
Russell.

04:21.084 --> 04:23.591
Dirty Uncle Russell? Really?

04:25.498 --> 04:28.758
- He'll promise her an Oscar.
- Promised me an Oscar.

04:28.760 --> 04:31.076
So I finally got my own show.

04:31.101 --> 04:33.941
I was 42... exactly like my dad.

04:33.966 --> 04:36.378
I mean, I was a real
slave to that narrative.

04:36.403 --> 04:38.434
And then I took the first seminar...

04:38.436 --> 04:41.671
Demystifying Happiness... and
it changed the game totally.

04:41.673 --> 04:44.151
It... it blew my mind.

04:44.612 --> 04:46.576
Well, I think it's great
that your so connected

04:46.578 --> 04:48.041
to what got you here.

04:49.991 --> 04:52.920
- Now go discover where you're going.
- Hmm.

04:52.945 --> 04:55.184
- Hello, darling.
- Hello.

04:55.186 --> 04:56.986
That's why I hate
parties. I'm going home.

04:56.988 --> 04:58.287
No, you are not.

04:58.289 --> 04:59.756
Hey, Megan.

04:59.758 --> 05:02.258
- Quick picture, please?
- God.

05:02.709 --> 05:04.927
- Oh, more.
- Beautiful.

05:04.929 --> 05:07.063
- Oh, should we do...
- Oh, yeah.

05:07.065 --> 05:09.165
Oh, yeah, yeah, yeah.

05:09.167 --> 05:11.667
- Love your shoes.
- Thank you.

05:15.234 --> 05:18.436
Now, that is a fierce-looking crew.

05:19.170 --> 05:21.711
Kyle, these are my
friends Hope and Shaun.

05:21.713 --> 05:24.391
- It's so nice to finally meet...
- I'm going on for hugs.

05:24.416 --> 05:26.017
- Oh. Okay.
- Get over here.

05:26.042 --> 05:27.587
I've heard so much about you both.

05:27.612 --> 05:29.185
- Hi.
- How you doing?

05:29.187 --> 05:32.046
Oh, your house is so gorgeous.

05:32.071 --> 05:33.204
Thank you, thank you.

05:33.229 --> 05:35.935
Megan actually says you have
a mid-century post and beam.

05:35.960 --> 05:37.446
I love that.

05:37.962 --> 05:40.096
And you... I saw your
episode of "Underage."

05:40.098 --> 05:42.832
- You were hilarious.
- Yeah, that's...

05:42.834 --> 05:43.992
I, um...

05:45.077 --> 05:47.202
He prepared.

05:47.483 --> 05:49.672
You're damn right I
prepared. Come on, let's go.

05:49.674 --> 05:51.474
Welcome.

05:51.476 --> 05:53.910
You know, we should actually
put her on Andres's radar.

05:53.912 --> 05:56.483
Oh, my God, it's so nice in here.

05:56.508 --> 05:57.983
You're gonna love him.

05:58.008 --> 06:00.293
He's not as depressed
as he looks, I promise.

06:00.318 --> 06:02.251
Oh, okay. Well, who's Andreas?

06:02.276 --> 06:03.898
Is, like, a Institute of the
Higher Mind shaman or something?

06:03.923 --> 06:06.422
No. Andres Plang, he's the
director of "The Kill Plan."

06:06.424 --> 06:07.828
Oh, Jesus.

06:07.853 --> 06:09.224
Did you put Kyle up to this?

06:09.249 --> 06:11.294
No, he just thought about it right now.

06:11.296 --> 06:14.263
- Don't be nervous.
- I'm not nervous. Just...

06:14.265 --> 06:17.800
you know, the whole "who you
know" thing is so obvious.

06:17.802 --> 06:20.937
All right. Never mind, then.
I'll introduce you to Terrence.

06:20.939 --> 06:23.005
He's already a big fan
of your Instagram page.

06:23.030 --> 06:24.499
Oh, I'll say hi to Terrence, yeah.

06:24.524 --> 06:26.223
No, I'll kick him in the nuts for you.

06:26.248 --> 06:28.535
It's 50/50 he wears some
sort of protective device.

06:28.560 --> 06:30.360
Look, how many shifts
did you cover for me

06:30.385 --> 06:32.168
when I had an audition, huh?

06:32.193 --> 06:33.560
Let me pay you back.

06:33.585 --> 06:35.808
Andres can help you.

06:35.887 --> 06:37.987
- Andres.
- Megan.

06:37.989 --> 06:40.423
- You look so dapper.
- And you look stunning.

06:40.425 --> 06:43.192
Oh, thank you.

06:43.194 --> 06:46.295
This is my very good friend Hope Declan.

06:46.297 --> 06:48.401
- Nice to meet you.
- Hi.

06:48.426 --> 06:50.499
Are you waiting for somebody?

06:50.501 --> 06:52.635
Oh, no.

06:52.637 --> 06:55.504
Just, um, trying to
figure this party out.

06:57.177 --> 06:58.644
So is everybody here

06:58.669 --> 07:00.443
with the Institute of the Higher Mind?

07:00.445 --> 07:02.712
'Cause if people are gonna
start handing out pamphlets...

07:02.714 --> 07:05.909
Oh, pamphlets. That's
what I forgot at home.

07:06.292 --> 07:09.051
And you're with the Institute.

07:10.082 --> 07:12.291
I teach the introductory
workshop. But don't worry...

07:12.316 --> 07:14.322
- I didn't come over here to recruit.
- Wow.

07:14.347 --> 07:16.110
Oh, so you have good intentions?

07:16.135 --> 07:18.671
Oh, well, I didn't say that.

07:20.431 --> 07:22.947
- Oh.
- I'm James.

07:23.268 --> 07:25.468
- Adam.
- We need to talk.

07:25.470 --> 07:27.003
Ugh, just don't tell me the story

07:27.005 --> 07:28.555
of your personal transformation, okay?

07:28.580 --> 07:31.040
I'm losing my shit. Does that count?

07:31.042 --> 07:33.156
Kyle's new friend...

07:33.648 --> 07:35.953
Okay, let's talk.

07:36.247 --> 07:38.014
I had her deal on my desk for three days

07:38.016 --> 07:40.717
waiting for my approval, but
I haven't even touched it.

07:40.742 --> 07:42.952
I know Kyle and Andres
say she's brilliant.

07:42.954 --> 07:44.353
And the head of the studio said

07:44.355 --> 07:45.988
they could cast whoever they want.

07:45.990 --> 07:47.734
I know what I said, but...

07:47.759 --> 07:50.092
at the end of the day, I
have a franchise to launch,

07:50.094 --> 07:52.104
and nobody knows who this girl is.

07:52.129 --> 07:53.462
So now you want to reject the deal

07:53.464 --> 07:55.398
that you've already
agreed to in principle?

07:55.400 --> 07:57.533
Yes, I want to be that asshole.

07:57.535 --> 07:59.468
Look, wouldn't you feel more comfortable

07:59.470 --> 08:01.522
with a recognizable name?

08:02.407 --> 08:04.206
I'm not your problem, Adam.

08:04.208 --> 08:07.276
I know, but maybe you can
talk to my problem for me.

08:11.115 --> 08:13.850
I'm not dropping that grenade
tonight, and neither are you.

08:13.875 --> 08:16.117
It stays between us for now.

08:16.220 --> 08:17.520
Oh.

08:17.522 --> 08:20.086
You boys talking business without me?

08:20.477 --> 08:22.656
- I have a situation.
- No.

08:25.029 --> 08:28.256
Well, when "Underage" ended,
I just sort of felt like I...

08:28.281 --> 08:30.039
you know, I'd kind of
done everything, you know,

08:30.064 --> 08:33.311
which is the goal for a while...
just, you know, keep working.

08:33.336 --> 08:35.104
Don't ask questions.

08:35.106 --> 08:37.006
I just sort of feel
like now I need to be

08:37.030 --> 08:39.785
a little more selective with my roles.

08:39.811 --> 08:41.610
Mm-hmm. Yeah.

08:41.611 --> 08:43.592
I feel like... maybe it's
like dating, you know?

08:43.616 --> 08:46.315
It's, um... just kind of hooking
up with everybody, and it's awesome,

08:46.317 --> 08:48.451
and then one day you
wake up, and you realize,

08:48.453 --> 08:51.530
"Maybe I should really
be looking for Mr. Right."

08:51.555 --> 08:53.813
So that's kind of where I'm
at. I'm looking for my... my...

08:53.815 --> 08:55.568
my Mr. Right project.

08:55.593 --> 08:57.561
I wish you luck with that.

08:57.586 --> 08:58.594
- Thank you.
- Just excuse me.

08:58.619 --> 08:59.688
- Uh, Russell.
- Yeah, no worries.

08:59.713 --> 09:00.742
- Andres.
- Yeah.

09:00.767 --> 09:03.727
- Come meet a friend with me.
- No more actresses, please.

09:10.767 --> 09:13.175
- Hope, are you okay?
- Yeah. No, I'm great.

09:13.177 --> 09:15.544
Um, scotch. What do you have?

09:18.344 --> 09:19.749
You're doing amazing.

09:19.751 --> 09:21.450
Oh, hold on. There's one more
person I want you to meet.

09:21.452 --> 09:22.852
Wait, wait, wait. Stop, stop.

09:22.854 --> 09:25.219
Can I just stop and tell you

09:25.244 --> 09:27.375
how wonderful you are?

09:27.400 --> 09:29.759
- No, you may not.
- I'm serious.

09:29.761 --> 09:34.096
The way you've set all this
up and welcomed my friends

09:34.098 --> 09:36.599
and just everything about this night...

09:36.601 --> 09:39.104
I'm really grateful for it all.

09:39.471 --> 09:41.470
I'm really grateful for you.

09:45.410 --> 09:47.176
Kyle? Can I talk to you outside?

09:47.178 --> 09:48.861
Hold on. One second.

09:50.081 --> 09:51.714
What is it?

09:53.184 --> 09:55.939
Miss Morrison.

09:56.033 --> 09:57.566
Ah.

09:57.854 --> 10:00.143
What up, party people?

10:00.168 --> 10:01.957
- Hey.
- Hey.

10:03.761 --> 10:05.394
Oh, how did it go with Andres?

10:05.396 --> 10:07.663
Oh, great, yeah. No,
he totally loves me.

10:07.665 --> 10:10.789
Um, I'm just not really sure
if he's my kind of director.

10:11.838 --> 10:13.012
- Megan.
- Yeah?

10:13.037 --> 10:15.546
- This is James.
- Oh.

10:15.571 --> 10:18.274
- Hello, James.
- Hello.

10:18.276 --> 10:21.010
Nice to meet the person everyone
wants a glimpse of tonight.

10:21.012 --> 10:22.569
Oh, stop.

10:22.594 --> 10:24.781
No, don't act like you don't know.

10:24.783 --> 10:26.993
This is your moment, girl.

10:27.018 --> 10:29.553
- This is happening.
- Hello.

10:29.578 --> 10:31.253
- Yes.
- Give me this.

10:31.255 --> 10:32.477
Take it.

10:32.502 --> 10:34.571
A-and everyone loves
Megan at the studio.

10:34.659 --> 10:36.555
Don't get us wrong, but
if we had another name

10:36.580 --> 10:38.071
on the poster with you,

10:38.096 --> 10:40.149
we're talking "Iron Man" territory...

10:40.174 --> 10:42.853
three huge films over
five to eight years

10:42.878 --> 10:44.811
and significantly less pressure on you,

10:44.836 --> 10:46.702
which is never a bad thing.

10:48.706 --> 10:51.474
- What do you think?
- Terrence?

10:55.525 --> 10:57.319
It's hard not to see the upside.

10:57.344 --> 10:59.953
Again, we can't wait to work with Megan.

10:59.978 --> 11:02.384
I-it's just about
finding the right project.

11:03.430 --> 11:05.555
Yeah. No, I-I hear you.

11:06.234 --> 11:08.891
Yeah, well, I want to make
sure that you both hear me.

11:10.928 --> 11:12.828
I'm the upside.

11:12.853 --> 11:16.109
I put the asses in the seats
no matter who's on the poster.

11:16.134 --> 11:18.567
And this is the right project for Megan,

11:18.592 --> 11:22.163
so you better close the deal
and put her in the movie... now,

11:22.188 --> 11:24.162
'cause I promise you, if you don't...

11:26.878 --> 11:29.093
there isn't gonna be a movie.

11:30.274 --> 11:31.982
Enjoy the party.

11:39.569 --> 11:41.217
_

11:43.052 --> 11:45.436
_

11:46.557 --> 11:48.393
- Hi.
- Hi.

11:50.805 --> 11:52.053
- Kyle.
- Yeah, man.

11:52.055 --> 11:54.022
- Yeah, it looked great.
- Excuse me.

11:54.047 --> 11:55.622
My deal just closed.

11:55.624 --> 11:57.788
- What?
- Yes.

11:59.946 --> 12:01.452
It would've been nice
to have your support

12:01.477 --> 12:03.064
when Kyle drew his line in the sand.

12:03.066 --> 12:04.732
I didn't agree with your take on it.

12:05.100 --> 12:08.130
Besides, Adam should've
come to me. I'm the producer.

12:08.155 --> 12:09.771
I really don't think he
makes the distinction.

12:09.773 --> 12:10.972
Of course he does.

12:10.974 --> 12:12.507
He knew I'd react the same way Kyle did.

12:12.532 --> 12:14.599
That's why he came to
you in the first place.

12:14.711 --> 12:16.511
This isn't about Megan's talent

12:16.513 --> 12:18.061
or how right she is for the role.

12:18.086 --> 12:20.315
It's about the fact that
she's not a household name.

12:20.317 --> 12:22.530
We're not getting caught up in that.

12:23.233 --> 12:25.485
By all means, stay above the fray.

12:25.510 --> 12:27.299
But if this movie's a flop,

12:27.324 --> 12:29.245
the entire town will know
that Kyle tanked a movie

12:29.270 --> 12:31.025
to get his girlfriend a part.

12:36.037 --> 12:38.266
Bravo. Our leading lady.

12:40.357 --> 12:43.371
- There you are.
- There I am.

12:43.373 --> 12:45.160
Oh, look, there's Andres.

12:45.185 --> 12:46.777
- Hi, Andres. Hi.
- Hello.

12:46.802 --> 12:48.567
Love this guy.

12:48.592 --> 12:51.713
And he loves actresses.
Did you know that?

12:51.715 --> 12:54.482
He just loves meeting
them and talking with them.

12:54.484 --> 12:57.218
He's just an overall
great lover of actresses.

12:58.522 --> 13:00.188
Did you know Megan's an actress?

13:00.190 --> 13:04.259
She's also my best friend,
and we are ride or die.

13:04.261 --> 13:05.727
And if you don't know what
that means, I'll tell you.

13:05.729 --> 13:09.130
It means that we don't take shit...

13:09.132 --> 13:10.532
from anybody!

13:12.836 --> 13:15.912
We are all ride or die up in here,

13:15.937 --> 13:17.748
- and you and I need a drink.
- Mm.

13:17.773 --> 13:19.908
- Yeah, all right. I hear that.
- All right.

13:19.910 --> 13:21.422
Peace!

13:21.601 --> 13:23.154
Sorry about that.

13:25.282 --> 13:26.586
It's the bar, right here.

13:26.611 --> 13:28.342
- We're not going to the bar.
- What?

13:28.367 --> 13:30.391
Zach, can you have Jesse
get the car ready, please?

13:30.416 --> 13:32.987
- Yeah.
- Get the car ready? What is this?

13:32.989 --> 13:34.856
I am gonna have my guy take you home.

13:34.858 --> 13:36.958
Oh, I don't need your
guy to take me home.

13:36.960 --> 13:38.526
See, 'cause I just got here.

13:38.528 --> 13:40.595
And you definitely had some fun,

13:40.597 --> 13:43.331
but we need to sit the
rest of this one out.

13:45.052 --> 13:47.357
Why don't you drive me home?

13:48.338 --> 13:50.705
Sweetie... there's a lot
of great things happening

13:50.707 --> 13:52.551
for your friend right now.

13:52.576 --> 13:55.429
Trust me, you don't
want to screw that up.

13:57.846 --> 13:59.247
Now get some rest.

14:04.721 --> 14:06.754
Yeah. Thanks.

14:15.377 --> 14:16.531
