- This is crazy.

15:04.020 --> 15:06.481
goes towards realizing
the vision of fashion

15:06.483 --> 15:07.963
as an instrument of change.

15:07.988 --> 15:10.192
Which means backing
up-and-coming designers

15:10.217 --> 15:11.894
who have pledged to abide by strict

15:11.919 --> 15:13.424
- environmental and social values
- _

15:13.449 --> 15:15.156
as they create their lines.

15:15.158 --> 15:18.167
We have one of these very
talented designers with us tonight,

15:18.192 --> 15:19.933
Maxwell Davis,

15:20.163 --> 15:22.307
who designed the dress
I'm very fortunate

15:22.332 --> 15:24.019
to be wearing right now.

15:24.044 --> 15:25.254
Thank you.

15:25.320 --> 15:26.648
Thank you all for coming.

15:26.729 --> 15:28.962
Please enjoy yourselves and, uh,

15:28.987 --> 15:30.218
keep those checks coming.

15:31.620 --> 15:33.319
- Way to go.
- Megan...

15:33.344 --> 15:35.351
- I need to speak with you.
- Now?

15:35.376 --> 15:36.961
Yeah, now.

15:38.862 --> 15:40.327
Okay.

15:40.352 --> 15:41.492
That's you, right?

15:41.517 --> 15:43.476
Jesus. What the hell is this?

15:43.501 --> 15:46.321
I don't know. Someone got your photos.

15:46.355 --> 15:48.766
- Oh, my God.
- I know.

15:48.791 --> 15:50.758
What's going on?

15:52.161 --> 15:54.719
All I can think is it... it was Nic.

15:55.024 --> 15:56.964
You know, he took the photos.

15:56.966 --> 15:58.983
And I haven't been returning his calls.

15:59.008 --> 16:00.968
How long ago did he take them?

16:00.970 --> 16:03.022
A year maybe.

16:03.047 --> 16:05.343
- So he has copies.
- No. No, no.

16:05.368 --> 16:06.945
I took them with my phone,

16:06.970 --> 16:09.093
and I deleted them months ago.

16:09.118 --> 16:11.045
But did you delete them off the cloud?

16:11.047 --> 16:13.876
Oh, God. The goddamn cloud.

16:13.901 --> 16:15.501
That's how he could've gotten them.

16:15.526 --> 16:16.829
Not in the last couple weeks.

16:16.854 --> 16:18.814
I mean, we encrypted everything
after Venice, didn't we?

16:18.839 --> 16:20.478
Yeah, we did,

16:20.503 --> 16:23.642
after we had the same problem
with another one of her friends.

16:25.152 --> 16:27.406
Sorry. People are wondering
whether they should go home.

16:28.597 --> 16:30.893
Yeah. Yeah, they should go home.

16:30.918 --> 16:32.284
Okay.

16:33.735 --> 16:35.441
The photos are everywhere.

16:35.466 --> 16:37.585
There isn't really
anything that we can do.

16:38.107 --> 16:40.574
Well, I'm gonna call Adam.
He should hear this from us.

16:40.576 --> 16:42.960
I'm sorry. You're concerned
about Adam right now?

16:47.254 --> 16:50.849
Well, the upside is
that you don't look awful

16:50.874 --> 16:53.179
and attention spans are short.

17:05.567 --> 17:08.244
- Hi.
- We have a problem.

17:08.270 --> 17:09.847
You saw the photos?

17:09.872 --> 17:11.739
Preteens in China have seen the photos.

17:11.763 --> 17:13.098
That's not the problem.

17:13.124 --> 17:15.376
Remember when I said I was
trying to get rid of the studio's

17:15.377 --> 17:17.077
ticky-tack bullshit in the contract?

17:17.079 --> 17:18.097
Yeah?

17:18.122 --> 17:19.810
Well, one of the things
I couldn't get rid of

17:19.835 --> 17:21.519
was the morality clause.

17:21.544 --> 17:23.884
- What the hell is that?
- It basically said

17:23.886 --> 17:27.153
that if you do anything
to bring disrepute,

17:27.178 --> 17:29.923
public ridicule, or
scandal to the project,

17:29.925 --> 17:31.825
they can terminate your contract.

17:31.827 --> 17:33.861
- Well, how is that relevant?
- Oh, sweetie,

17:33.863 --> 17:36.730
because the rumor is you
leaked the photos yourself

17:36.732 --> 17:38.457
as a publicity grab.

17:38.482 --> 17:39.902
What?

17:40.369 --> 17:42.569
Well... hold on. I have...
I have to call you back.

17:42.571 --> 17:43.870
What's going on?

17:43.895 --> 17:46.674
Apparently it's out there
that I did this myself,

17:46.676 --> 17:49.009
and Leslie says there's
a morality clause

17:49.011 --> 17:50.886
in the "Kill Plan" contract.

17:50.911 --> 17:53.247
So basically they can fire me.

17:54.020 --> 17:56.526
I don't understand who would do this.

18:21.125 --> 18:23.055
_

18:23.080 --> 18:25.314
_

18:27.895 --> 18:29.598
_

18:33.923 --> 18:36.102
_

18:36.127 --> 18:38.202
_

18:38.227 --> 18:40.951
Yeah, did he know about
the morality clause?

18:41.397 --> 18:43.097
Kyle, I know what you're thinking.

18:43.099 --> 18:44.974
No, just tell me.

18:45.302 --> 18:46.808
Yes, he knew.

18:46.833 --> 18:48.138
Adam wants us to come to the studio.

18:48.163 --> 18:51.435
- Can you be there in an hour?
- Yeah. See you soon.

19:01.775 --> 19:03.650
Hey, stop.

19:07.901 --> 19:10.468
How am I gonna prove
that I didn't do this?

19:12.806 --> 19:14.528
You're not.

19:14.530 --> 19:16.196
You're gonna pack a bag,

19:16.198 --> 19:18.321
and we're gonna get the hell out of L.A.

19:52.999 --> 19:55.366
- Beautiful, isn't it?
- Yeah.

19:56.337 --> 19:58.100
You come here a lot?

19:58.320 --> 19:59.912
Not enough.

20:00.206 --> 20:03.294
I'm usually pretty good at blocking
out all the noise in my life,

20:03.319 --> 20:05.006
but when it gets too tough,

20:05.031 --> 20:06.311
I come here.

20:06.336 --> 20:08.690
There's no Internet,
no cell phone service.

20:08.715 --> 20:11.148
It's like the outside
world doesn't even exist.

20:12.952 --> 20:14.873
It just got tough for you?

20:14.898 --> 20:16.585
It's not for me.

20:16.610 --> 20:18.350
This is for you.

20:19.325 --> 20:20.486
Come on.

20:20.511 --> 20:22.660
There are naked photographs
of your girlfriend

20:22.662 --> 20:24.395
taken by another guy,

20:24.397 --> 20:27.440
and everything people are
saying about them and me...

20:27.791 --> 20:30.010
it all reflects back to you.

20:30.035 --> 20:32.246
Not to mention the
studio is freaking out.

20:32.271 --> 20:33.572
Well...

20:33.597 --> 20:36.650
let everybody else get
caught up in all the bullshit.

20:37.343 --> 20:40.900
We'll focus on what actually matters.

20:42.604 --> 20:44.196
You know what?

20:44.261 --> 20:46.032
Look where we are.

20:46.919 --> 20:48.886
You want to take a walk?

20:50.718 --> 20:52.148
Come on.

20:54.397 --> 20:56.538
Okay, Kyle, I'm hoping you're
not in a ditch somewhere

20:56.563 --> 20:58.296
so I'd really appreciate
it if you called me

20:58.321 --> 21:00.077
and told me why you're
not here right now.

21:01.212 --> 21:03.062
He's obviously turned his phone off.

21:03.087 --> 21:04.252
Kyle's making a statement.

21:04.277 --> 21:06.037
I'm getting real familiar with it.

21:06.039 --> 21:07.422
There's no room for conversation.

21:07.447 --> 21:09.789
It's just his way or no way at all.

21:09.814 --> 21:11.351
It's not a conversation, Adam.

21:11.376 --> 21:13.943
It's you using the morality
clause to try and strong-arm him

21:13.968 --> 21:16.156
into doing something that
he doesn't want to do.

21:16.441 --> 21:18.575
I wasn't the one who
wanted it in the contract.

21:18.600 --> 21:19.984
Well, you're certainly
taking advantage of it.

21:20.009 --> 21:21.708
We have no proof that
Megan leaked the photos.

21:21.733 --> 21:23.333
Who says I need proof?

21:23.823 --> 21:26.471
It's already out there.
That's what matters.

21:28.898 --> 21:32.333
At the Institute, they always
say, "Life is a living thing."

21:32.515 --> 21:34.549
Life is a living thing.

21:35.568 --> 21:36.893
What it means is...

21:36.918 --> 21:39.313
life is constantly
changing moment to moment.

21:39.338 --> 21:42.206
I had heard it a thousand
times, and I was always like,

21:42.208 --> 21:44.588
"Yeah. Yeah, yeah, it is."

21:45.361 --> 21:47.845
Then when Lisbeth left me,

21:47.847 --> 21:50.214
I realized that I didn't
understand anything.

21:50.680 --> 21:53.516
Couldn't eat, couldn't get out of bed.

21:54.682 --> 21:55.829
And everything that I had learned

21:55.854 --> 21:58.282
was just a bunch of
useless clutter in my head.

22:00.235 --> 22:02.269
Then I saw this place.

22:03.505 --> 22:05.830
And for some reason, I stopped

22:05.832 --> 22:07.927
and just sat here and
watched the current.

22:09.325 --> 22:11.465
And it all started to make sense.

22:12.205 --> 22:13.838
Life is always moving.

22:13.840 --> 22:16.637
It's always taking us somewhere,
whether we see it or not.

22:17.566 --> 22:19.488
Nothing's permanent...

22:20.713 --> 22:22.613
least of all feelings.

22:31.824 --> 22:33.947
Where does this stream go?

22:38.189 --> 22:40.570
To a sewage plant about a mile away.

22:43.056 --> 22:46.003
- That's perfect.
- That's right.

22:47.840 --> 22:49.673
Do you mind if I order a glass of wine?

22:49.698 --> 22:51.184
Do you mind if I show you pictures

22:51.209 --> 22:52.926
of how we're decorating the nursery?

22:52.951 --> 22:55.185
- Sparkling water, please.
- Two.

22:57.049 --> 22:58.849
I appreciate you meeting me.

22:58.851 --> 23:01.402
I'm sure you're already
trying to convince Megan

23:01.427 --> 23:04.128
to fire me and move to CAA.

23:04.219 --> 23:05.707
Not yet.

23:06.936 --> 23:09.778
Well, that'll be a conversation
for a different time.

23:11.238 --> 23:13.783
Since I know Megan better than anyone,

23:13.808 --> 23:15.863
I thought maybe we could talk
about how to make the most

23:15.888 --> 23:20.283
of a very unfortunate situation.

23:20.308 --> 23:22.039
What did you have in mind?

23:22.041 --> 23:23.627
Focusing on the ex.

23:23.652 --> 23:26.477
You know, he forced her
into taking the pictures,

23:26.479 --> 23:28.913
and then he leaked them
when she had the courage

23:28.915 --> 23:32.588
to get out of a borderline
abusive relationship.

23:32.613 --> 23:34.899
That is very zeitgeist, D.

23:34.924 --> 23:37.760
Or we could just let the
whole thing blow over.

23:40.193 --> 23:42.159
Why leak the photos

23:42.161 --> 23:45.176
if you don't want to
make the most of them?

23:46.150 --> 23:48.637
You think I leaked the photos?

23:54.040 --> 23:55.489
Thanks.

23:56.122 --> 23:57.552
Little Megan in that big

23:57.592 --> 23:59.566
$200 million blockbuster?

23:59.606 --> 24:02.856
Come on. Adam Westfield had
to be shitting his pants.

24:02.881 --> 24:05.028
It's so much easier for you

24:05.084 --> 24:07.929
if suddenly the world knows who she is.

24:09.066 --> 24:11.179
It's easier for you, too.

24:11.657 --> 24:13.163
Maybe.

24:13.259 --> 24:15.859
But I'm not the one who had an IT guy

24:15.861 --> 24:18.062
at her house two weeks ago.

24:19.465 --> 24:21.366
I didn't leak the photos.

24:21.621 --> 24:22.944
Good.

24:24.810 --> 24:27.085
You can go ahead and order your wine.

24:33.546 --> 24:34.906
Kyle.

24:36.088 --> 24:37.339
Kyle.

24:37.450 --> 24:39.583
- Mm. Come here.
- No, stop, stop.

24:39.585 --> 24:41.524
What... what happened?

24:41.787 --> 24:43.438
Nothing.

24:43.463 --> 24:44.906
What?

24:45.580 --> 24:49.360
An hour ago, we were
totally connected, and now...

24:49.642 --> 24:52.398
I don't know, you're not
here, and I could feel it.

24:53.023 --> 24:54.222
I'm here, baby.

24:54.247 --> 24:55.980
- I'm right here.
- No...

24:58.295 --> 25:00.069
Is this about the photos?

25:00.094 --> 25:01.527
'Cause that would make total sense.

25:01.552 --> 25:03.986
Megan, I'm not thinking
about the photos.

25:04.110 --> 25:06.622
Can you just relax about that?

25:06.647 --> 25:10.347
I just want to know why you're
checked out while you kiss me.

25:10.349 --> 25:13.032
And don't tell me that
you're not, all right?

25:13.057 --> 25:14.978
I'm familiar with it.

25:15.541 --> 25:17.041
I don't know what I'm supposed to say.

25:17.066 --> 25:18.889
Maybe you want to tell me that, too.

25:19.321 --> 25:21.959
Wow. Okay, is this,
uh, annoying for you?

25:21.961 --> 25:24.273
Yeah, a little bit, yeah.

25:24.664 --> 25:26.196
You know...

25:26.198 --> 25:29.466
you gave me this long
speech about your past,

25:29.468 --> 25:30.934
and now it's me.

25:30.936 --> 25:33.904
And right now you have nothing?

25:35.383 --> 25:36.907
So this is about Lisbeth?

25:36.909 --> 25:38.575
- Figures.
- No.

25:38.577 --> 25:39.943
It's about you, Kyle,

25:39.945 --> 25:42.695
but maybe now I finally
know why she left.

25:45.516 --> 25:46.977
I'm sorry.

25:48.120 --> 25:49.787
Hey, I'm gonna... I'm gonna take a walk.

25:56.428 --> 25:58.301
Kyle!

25:59.184 --> 26:01.031
Kyle?

26:04.265 --> 26:05.929
Kyle.

26:06.226 --> 26:08.390
I'm sorry.

26:09.071 --> 26:10.537
Oh.

26:10.562 --> 26:13.304
Kyle, please talk to me.

26:28.749 --> 26:30.449
- You okay?
- I'm fine.

26:30.451 --> 26:32.917
I tripped. That branch is
not supposed to be there.

26:32.942 --> 26:34.472
Yeah, that's what the flashlight's for.

26:34.497 --> 26:36.163
Well, I wasn't shining it down.

26:36.188 --> 26:39.289
I was shining it out because
I was looking for you...

26:39.493 --> 26:41.126
and also bears.

26:51.272 --> 26:53.872
I'm sorry for what I said.

26:53.874 --> 26:55.674
It was horrible.

26:59.066 --> 27:00.527
You were right.

27:00.552 --> 27:02.652
I wasn't being honest.

27:03.651 --> 27:05.863
Those pictures got to me.

27:06.086 --> 27:08.669
It's not that you were naked
or even with another dude.

27:08.694 --> 27:10.728
I mean, we all have a past.

27:10.978 --> 27:13.660
But I saw that smile on your face.

27:14.240 --> 27:16.310
My smile?

27:18.546 --> 27:19.888
Look...

27:20.334 --> 27:22.497
in one of those pictures, you were...

27:24.648 --> 27:26.794
you were smiling in
this incredible way...

27:26.819 --> 27:28.974
at Nic, I guess.

27:28.999 --> 27:30.825
But I recognized it,

27:31.076 --> 27:34.763
'cause you smiled at me the
exact same way in Mexico.

27:37.101 --> 27:40.153
It just... it scared the shit
out of me to think that...

27:42.323 --> 27:44.200
like, I mean, we talked about
it today, right? I mean...

27:44.225 --> 27:47.114
everything changes. Nothing's permanent.

27:48.128 --> 27:49.591
Kyle...

27:49.616 --> 27:51.505
It's ju... I don't want
us to end up with nothing

27:51.530 --> 27:53.497
except some photos and...

27:54.568 --> 27:56.927
a bunch of shitty feelings.

27:57.671 --> 27:59.605
I can't do that again.

28:02.910 --> 28:04.610
I love you.

28:11.917 --> 28:13.644
I love you, too.

28:53.794 --> 28:55.093
What are you doing?

28:55.095 --> 28:57.106
I have to pee badly.

28:57.131 --> 28:59.012
Well, you can just go
right outside the door.

28:59.037 --> 29:01.371
- I'm going to.
- Why you getting dressed?

29:01.435 --> 29:03.235
You scared the bears
are gonna see you naked?

29:06.829 --> 29:08.073
What?

29:08.230 --> 29:11.665
I'm not scared of
anyone seeing me naked.

29:15.559 --> 29:17.016
Okay.

29:17.695 --> 29:19.256
You sure you're okay with this?

29:19.281 --> 29:21.601
I am more than okay
with this, all right?

29:21.626 --> 29:23.305
I love this idea.

29:24.008 --> 29:25.320
All right.

29:25.945 --> 29:27.893
Naked in the woods.

29:27.895 --> 29:30.329
- Naked in the woods.
- Whoo!

29:30.331 --> 29:33.264
- Taking my power back.
- Get that power back.

29:33.289 --> 29:36.172
Okay, I think I'm warm enough now.

29:36.305 --> 29:39.328
And I'm already screwed with
this morality-clause thing,

29:39.353 --> 29:42.391
so don't be afraid to go a little sexy.

29:47.448 --> 29:49.621
You know what? This isn't right.

29:49.646 --> 29:52.763
What? No. What do you mean?
This is... this is totally right.

29:52.974 --> 29:55.787
No, it isn't, not yet.

30:02.796 --> 30:04.763
Kyle just showed up.

30:04.765 --> 30:07.529
- He's here?
- Not exactly.

30:12.551 --> 30:14.317
It's already got a million likes.

30:14.342 --> 30:15.807
Yeah, I can see that.

30:15.809 --> 30:18.075
_

30:18.379 --> 30:20.497
- Try him again.
- Okay.

30:22.256 --> 30:24.786
Uh, a-actually, don't.
Get me Adam instead.

30:24.811 --> 30:26.419
O-okay.

30:27.021 --> 30:29.054
Adam Westfield's office, please.

30:31.044 --> 30:32.591
And there she is. I mean, look,

30:32.623 --> 30:35.255
this girl has absolutely zero training,

30:35.271 --> 30:36.938
but yet her instincts are amazing.

30:36.940 --> 30:38.139
She reframed the narrative.

30:38.141 --> 30:39.941
She came up with the idea herself.

30:39.943 --> 30:42.075
I had to do it with her.

30:43.713 --> 30:45.313
Well, hey, there's nothing
like getting your penis

30:45.315 --> 30:46.597
in the public record, right?

30:48.495 --> 30:50.409
Look, the morality clause is dead.

30:50.434 --> 30:53.330
If they want to bounce her,
they got to bounce me, too.

30:53.690 --> 30:56.791
Now, B&A is doing a
piece on Internet shaming,

30:56.793 --> 30:58.409
and they want to interview us.

30:58.434 --> 31:00.924
I mean, we're spinning this
whole thing into a positive.

31:01.731 --> 31:03.214
So you're in a good place?

31:03.239 --> 31:05.290
I'm in a great place.

31:07.661 --> 31:09.222
And how about us? How are we?

31:13.080 --> 31:15.143
Okay, come on, man, let's just, uh...

31:15.145 --> 31:16.444
let's be real with each other.

31:16.446 --> 31:18.980
You think I leaked
those photos, don't you?

31:18.982 --> 31:22.517
Yes, or leaked the rumor
that Megan did it...

31:22.519 --> 31:24.034
or both.

31:25.288 --> 31:26.788
Well, thanks for being honest.

31:26.790 --> 31:28.243
Um, I'll do the same.

31:28.268 --> 31:29.555
Fire away.

31:30.126 --> 31:32.660
I haven't exactly been sold on Megan.

31:32.662 --> 31:34.429
I guess you've sensed that.

31:34.431 --> 31:36.664
She's... she's beautiful.
She's a good actress.

31:36.666 --> 31:40.034
But whatever this other thing is
that you and Deanne see in her,

31:40.036 --> 31:41.979
it's been lost on me...

31:42.004 --> 31:43.439
until now.

31:44.692 --> 31:46.325
She makes you happy.

31:46.350 --> 31:49.654
And I care about you, so I'm all-in...

31:50.728 --> 31:52.076
Truly.

31:55.152 --> 31:57.535
Thanks, man. That really
means the world to me.

31:59.037 --> 32:01.571
Look, nothing's more important
to me than your best interests,

32:01.596 --> 32:03.963
and Megan's best interests
are a big part of that now.

32:03.988 --> 32:05.426
We're all doing this together.

32:05.451 --> 32:07.215
That's exactly how I feel.

32:07.564 --> 32:09.197
Good...

32:09.199 --> 32:12.120
because an opportunity has just come up.

32:12.435 --> 32:14.268
Okay, so, you know,
we'll have a lead-in

32:14.270 --> 32:17.605
with some B-roll of, you know,
other celebrity photo leaks...

32:17.607 --> 32:19.688
you know, Kate Upton, Jennifer Lawrence.

32:19.713 --> 32:20.948
Then we're gonna cut to the interview.

32:20.973 --> 32:22.353
That's gonna go for about three minutes.

32:22.378 --> 32:23.818
You guys know how we do things.

32:23.843 --> 32:25.757
Just keep the energy up. Keep
it nice and conversational.

32:25.782 --> 32:28.553
And just so we're clear... she's
asking the approved questions only.

32:28.578 --> 32:31.270
That's the plan, but it is live TV.

32:31.481 --> 32:33.106
Yeah. Can someone explain to me

32:33.131 --> 32:35.037
the point of even doing
anything live anymore?

32:35.062 --> 32:36.614
It's antiquated.

32:36.639 --> 32:38.593
Oh, oh, okay. Oh, you want to quote me?

32:38.595 --> 32:40.092
Okay, how about this?

32:40.117 --> 32:41.763
It's bullshit.

32:41.765 --> 32:44.426
Brandon, I don't know where
you're getting your information,

32:44.451 --> 32:46.223
but you're gonna embarrass yourself.

32:46.248 --> 32:48.503
And my client has had
quite enough for one week,

32:48.505 --> 32:51.326
so move on, please.

32:54.474 --> 32:55.740
What's going on?

32:55.765 --> 32:57.810
Oh, they're Dumpster diving at Deadline.

32:57.835 --> 32:59.714
- Don't worry about it.
- What did he ask you?

32:59.716 --> 33:03.551
He wanted me to comment
on this nonsense rumor

33:03.553 --> 33:06.935
that Amelia Briggs has replaced
Megan in "The Kill Plan."

33:06.960 --> 33:08.156
That's a rumor?

33:08.158 --> 33:09.957
The keep getting better and better.

33:11.321 --> 33:12.841
Hey, come on, let's go talk.

33:12.866 --> 33:14.028
Wait. What?

33:14.030 --> 33:16.164
- What the hell is going on?
- I have no idea.

33:16.166 --> 33:18.861
So it's true? I'm being replaced?

33:18.886 --> 33:20.052
- Megan, Megan...
- Megan...

33:20.077 --> 33:22.057
Just tell me what the hell is going on.

33:23.706 --> 33:25.973
I got a call from
Amelia's rep yesterday.

33:25.975 --> 33:28.141
Dan Buckleman... he's a total prick,

33:28.166 --> 33:30.891
but he's Institute, so
we know how that works.

33:30.916 --> 33:32.313
We got lucky.

33:32.315 --> 33:34.682
She's dropping out of her
current project to do ours.

33:34.684 --> 33:36.984
She's box office equity.
It's a no-brainer.

33:36.986 --> 33:40.188
- So it's about money?
- For the studio.

33:40.213 --> 33:41.993
For me, it's about protecting you.

33:42.018 --> 33:44.025
I don't need you to protect me.

33:44.027 --> 33:46.594
And I'm sorry, but Amelia Briggs?

33:46.596 --> 33:48.429
Look, you were the better actor,

33:48.431 --> 33:50.965
but throwing you into a giant
franchise right out the gate,

33:50.967 --> 33:52.283
it's not in your best interests.

33:52.308 --> 33:54.542
Why don't you let Megan and
her agent make that decision?

33:54.567 --> 33:56.025
And why don't you let Kyle speak?

33:56.050 --> 33:57.588
Why don't you, Terrence?

33:57.613 --> 33:59.116
Your name isn't even on the movie.

33:59.142 --> 34:01.399
You get one chance to prove yourself.

34:01.424 --> 34:02.533
And I don't want everyone thinking

34:02.558 --> 34:04.096
you're only in the movie because of me.

34:04.121 --> 34:05.922
That will be the narrative.

34:05.947 --> 34:07.992
The whole world's gonna
want to see you fail,

34:08.016 --> 34:09.984
and I'm not gonna set you up for that.

34:10.657 --> 34:14.467
You felt completely different
about this two days ago.

34:14.493 --> 34:16.924
How do you just change
your mind like that?

34:16.926 --> 34:18.391
Look, come here.

34:22.998 --> 34:24.732
Jesus, Kyle.

34:24.734 --> 34:27.735
- I told you I love you.
- And I love you.

34:27.737 --> 34:29.063
Look, now the studio owes me,

34:29.088 --> 34:30.788
so they're gonna have to
let me direct the next movie.

34:30.813 --> 34:32.132
Oh. Oh, you're gonna direct.

34:32.158 --> 34:33.958
That was your trade-off
for getting rid of me?

34:33.983 --> 34:35.304
No, that's not what I'm saying.

34:35.330 --> 34:36.774
What I'm saying is...

34:36.884 --> 34:38.684
is that I'm gonna have
final approval on casting.

34:38.708 --> 34:40.553
We'll get to do the movie together.

34:40.578 --> 34:42.851
Look, I am dying to work with you.

34:44.882 --> 34:46.721
Until you're not.

34:46.723 --> 34:48.856
Okay, we are ready for you guys.

34:48.858 --> 34:51.092
That's too bad, because
there's no way in hell

34:51.094 --> 34:52.793
she's doing this interview now.

34:52.795 --> 34:54.594
I'm sorry. We're gonna have to cancel.

34:54.597 --> 34:55.868
You know what? I'm sure...

34:55.893 --> 34:58.086
No, we're gonna do it.

35:02.398 --> 35:04.252
Okay, then.

35:09.941 --> 35:12.341
And I'm just naked as
a bear in the woods.

35:12.415 --> 35:13.610
Really?

35:13.635 --> 35:15.782
And then all of a sudden, he
started taking off his clothes,

35:15.807 --> 35:17.531
and then I realized what he was doing.

35:17.556 --> 35:18.686
So...

35:18.688 --> 35:21.165
Well, look, she looked so cold.
I couldn't let her suffer alone.

35:21.190 --> 35:24.390
Well, you two made a beautiful picture

35:24.415 --> 35:27.001
that just happened to make an
important statement at the same time.

35:27.026 --> 35:28.118
Congratulations.

35:28.143 --> 35:29.542
And thank you so very much

35:29.567 --> 35:31.618
for taking the time to
sit down with me today.

35:31.643 --> 35:34.283
Actually, I'd like
to say something else.

35:35.885 --> 35:37.758
Oh, okay. Of course.

35:40.263 --> 35:43.821
There are people out there
who want to see you fail.

35:43.846 --> 35:46.062
And they'll look at everything
that happened the past few days

35:46.087 --> 35:49.617
and think, "Oh, well, look at
how much publicity she got."

35:49.619 --> 35:52.986
And all I can say about that is...

35:53.509 --> 35:56.190
that none of it is worth
spending a second of your life

35:56.192 --> 35:58.017
feeling powerless.

35:58.042 --> 36:00.726
And if there's anything
that this has taught me,

36:00.751 --> 36:04.798
it's that I can choose
not to feel powerless.

36:05.744 --> 36:08.269
And I'll never let that happen again.

36:11.407 --> 36:14.361
Megan is the most
powerful person I know.

36:14.837 --> 36:17.945
Well, you two make an incredible couple.

36:17.947 --> 36:20.552
Thank you again for
sitting down with me today.

36:20.577 --> 36:22.049
Thank you.

36:22.051 --> 36:24.147
And we're out.

36:24.733 --> 36:27.188
- Wow. Guys, that was great.
- Yeah, it was a pleasure.

36:27.190 --> 36:28.923
- Thank you. Great interview.
- Thanks.

36:28.925 --> 36:30.725
Very nice to meet you.

36:30.727 --> 36:32.059
Megan.

36:46.084 --> 36:49.442
So... have you talked to Megan?

36:49.466 --> 36:51.767
Mm, not since the party.

36:51.989 --> 36:53.902
She's too busy with her fake life.

36:53.904 --> 36:55.231
What are you talking about?

36:55.256 --> 36:58.250
Oh, I-I guess you didn't see
how she was acting that night.

36:58.275 --> 37:00.542
I saw how you were acting.

37:00.544 --> 37:02.711
Well, at least I was real.

37:02.713 --> 37:04.831
She ran around that party like,

37:04.856 --> 37:07.749
"Look at me. I'm
Hollywood's newest ingénue."

37:07.751 --> 37:09.442
Two weeks ago, I was
holding her hair back

37:09.467 --> 37:10.829
while she puked in bushes.

37:10.854 --> 37:13.192
I was actually the one holding her hair.

37:13.217 --> 37:16.104
Things change for people.
There's nothing wrong with that.

37:16.129 --> 37:18.226
She doesn't even return our calls.

37:18.228 --> 37:19.954
I can't believe you're cool with that.

37:19.979 --> 37:22.641
Are you seriously playing
the jilted friend right now?

37:22.666 --> 37:25.434
Oh, God, I can't believe
you don't see this.

37:25.436 --> 37:29.109
Her guy kicked me out of his party...

37:29.134 --> 37:32.187
- Hope, no he...
- And then passed me off to his driver,

37:32.212 --> 37:33.442
who totally manhandled me

37:33.444 --> 37:35.544
when I told him to piss off, by the way.

37:35.546 --> 37:36.681
You were pretty wasted.

37:36.706 --> 37:38.773
Are you sure that's how it went down?

37:39.016 --> 37:41.950
Kyle West is not a good guy.

37:41.952 --> 37:43.251
Shh.

37:43.253 --> 37:45.992
I saw it in his eyes. He's fake.

37:46.017 --> 37:48.876
He acts sweet and
perfect, and it's bullshit.

37:48.901 --> 37:52.275
He's really just a product of
the Institute of the Higher Mind,

37:52.563 --> 37:56.212
which I've also heard
terrible stories about.

37:57.118 --> 37:59.577
And now he's got his hooks into Megan.

37:59.618 --> 38:02.017
- I think that...
- She's getting totally sucked in,

38:02.042 --> 38:03.341
and it needs to stop,

38:03.366 --> 38:05.158
and that was the whole
point of the photos.

38:05.183 --> 38:06.845
Wait. What?

38:07.071 --> 38:09.759
You're the one who leaked the photos?

38:10.626 --> 38:12.481
Are you serious?

38:14.324 --> 38:16.134
Hope.

38:16.442 --> 38:17.765
Wha...

38:17.790 --> 38:19.367
How did you get them?

38:19.392 --> 38:21.022
I copied them from her phone

38:21.024 --> 38:22.624
when we were at Ace for New Year's,

38:22.626 --> 38:25.093
'cause I was gonna make her
a gag gift for her birthday,

38:25.095 --> 38:26.486
but...

38:26.511 --> 38:28.704
What? Don't do that.
Don't look at me like that.

38:28.729 --> 38:31.790
Oh, my God, this is sick, Hope.

38:33.118 --> 38:36.095
- It was for her own good.
- Oh, bullshit.

38:36.121 --> 38:38.517
That's bullshit. You want to be real?

38:38.675 --> 38:40.776
It was all about you.

38:40.778 --> 38:42.508
You saw yourself in Megan's rear-view

38:42.533 --> 38:44.212
the moment you walked into that party.

38:44.214 --> 38:46.248
You decided you weren't gonna fit in.

38:46.250 --> 38:47.828
Well, I tried.

38:47.853 --> 38:50.452
Well, a real friend would try harder.

38:50.454 --> 38:51.920
And if she can't do that,

38:51.922 --> 38:54.269
she would just get the
hell out of the way.

39:31.401 --> 39:33.764
I figured you weren't
answering your phone.

39:33.789 --> 39:35.554
You figured right.

39:35.812 --> 39:38.234
It's okay. I'm not gonna stay.

39:38.468 --> 39:40.148
What do you want, then?

39:40.955 --> 39:41.961
I want to tell you that...

39:41.986 --> 39:43.812
you handled yourself really
well at the studio today.

39:43.837 --> 39:46.867
I was very impressed, and, um...

39:47.890 --> 39:49.444
you know, as a woman in this business,

39:49.446 --> 39:52.714
you sometimes have to accept
things that you don't like

39:52.716 --> 39:54.953
because you have your
eye on a bigger prize.

39:55.328 --> 39:57.961
Look, I really don't want
another explanation right now.

39:57.986 --> 40:00.242
It's not an explanation, Megan.

40:01.365 --> 40:03.969
You know, I really came here to tell you

40:03.994 --> 40:06.942
that things aren't always gonna
be this way for you and me.

40:07.973 --> 40:11.132
We're not always going to
be the women behind the men.

40:11.134 --> 40:12.848
That's gonna change.

40:13.537 --> 40:15.294
I promise.

40:20.333 --> 40:23.583
Terrence. Sorry. She just kind of...

40:23.614 --> 40:25.046
It's fine.

40:25.048 --> 40:28.309
Mr. Anderson, I'm Detective Gaffe, LAPD.

40:29.090 --> 40:31.364
Sorry to interrupt. I didn't
realize that your organization

40:31.389 --> 40:33.317
endorsed that kind of stuff.

40:33.599 --> 40:36.734
Oh, moderation's the
key, like anything else.

40:36.916 --> 40:38.324
What can I do for you?

40:38.349 --> 40:40.762
Actually, I have a missing-persons case.

40:43.248 --> 40:45.144
Sofie Marchuk...
according to her family,

40:45.169 --> 40:47.412
she took courses at your institute.

40:47.437 --> 40:49.104
Do you have a couple minutes?

40:49.488 --> 40:52.168
- I just have a few questions.
- Absolutely.

40:52.504 --> 40:53.726
Great.

41:04.254 --> 41:05.463
Hey.

41:05.807 --> 41:08.775
I know you don't want to
talk to me, and I get it.

41:08.800 --> 41:10.700
I-I just want to say that...

41:10.725 --> 41:13.238
well, when you're ready, I'm here.

41:14.898 --> 41:16.865
Hey, the other option is...

41:16.867 --> 41:18.422
we don't have to talk.

41:18.447 --> 41:21.875
You can come over, scream
and yell and break stuff.

41:22.140 --> 41:24.203
I-I'm totally fine with that.

41:24.574 --> 41:26.617
Just putting that out there.

41:28.758 --> 41:31.727
Okay, I screwed this up.

41:31.752 --> 41:33.551
I love you, Megan.

41:33.576 --> 41:35.672
That's the first thing I should've said.

41:36.687 --> 41:38.149
I love you.

41:39.456 --> 41:41.016
That's it.

41:53.282 --> 41:56.289
So, I read that you
two met at an audition.

41:56.468 --> 41:59.687
- Is it a real story?
- That is a real story.

42:00.632 --> 42:02.375
Wow, you got a job and a boyfriend.

42:02.400 --> 42:03.805
Now, that's a good audition, girl.

42:03.829 --> 42:05.398
Just the boyfriend...

42:05.445 --> 42:07.256
but still a good audition.

42:07.281 --> 42:09.523
Tell the truth. Was
there really a movie?

42:09.554 --> 42:11.742
Or were you just auditioning
her to be your girlfriend?

42:11.767 --> 42:14.422
- Stop tripping.
- What? You don't think that happens?

42:14.447 --> 42:17.413
I mean, that's what they do at
the Institute of the Higher Mind

